  "text": "The latter approach tries to compute consistent query answers in response to a query i.e., answers that are true in every repair of the given database, but the source data is not fixed. Unfortunately, finding consistent answers to aggregate queries is a NP-complete problem already using two (or more) FDs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . To mitigate this problem, recently a number of works have exploited heuristics to find a database repair, as (Yakout et al., 2013; [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . They seem to be very promising approaches, even though their effectiveness has not been evaluated on real-world domains.",
